<HEADLINE>
CRAVEN TWINS PICK USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Twin brother basketball players Errick and Derrick
Craven of Bishop Montgomery High in Torrance have decided to attend
USC.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's close to home and my family will get to see me play,''
Derrick Craven said. ``I wanted to stay in California. We wanted to
be able to come home on the weekends.''
</P>
<P>
   Errick (6-foot-2, 170) is considered one of the top guards in
the West. He averaged 20.9 points, 7.3 rebounds, 3.7 assists and
3.6 steals as the twins led Bishop Montgomery to the Division III
state title last spring. Derrick (6-2, 170) averaged 17.1 points,
5.8 assists, 5.6 rebounds and 3.1 steals.
</P>
<P>
   Derrick Craven said the twins expected to officially inform USC
coaches on Thursday night of their decision.
</P>
<P>
   Other schools that recruited the twins were UCLA, Stanford and
California. Some colleges balked at taking both brothers, who
insisted on attending the same school.
</P>
<P>
   They are projected as combo guards in college, capable of
playing either the point or shooting guard position.
</P>
</TEXT>
