<P>
   &UR; MASKED BALL: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   The Philadelphia city council has passed a law making it illegal
to wear a mask with the intent of intimidating somebody. The
Republican Convention in the city may be targeted by Seattle-style
protesters. (Washington Post, June 26) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SOMEBODY STOP HIM: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Speculation that Ross Perot will challenge Pat Buchanan for the
Reform Party nomination is growing. The deadline for entering the
ballot is July 1. (Salon, June 28) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; RESPONSE OF THE WEEK: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   ``Our role is not to jump-start your campaign and all of a
sudden make you competitive.'' (Paul Kirk, co-chairman of the
Commission on Presidential Debates, responding to complaints by
Ralph Nader and Buchanan about being excluded from the debates.
Washington Post, June 22) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DUMB AND DUMBER (1): &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   ``If you give people the impression you're a smarty-pants,
that's no good for sure.'' (Al Gore, Time, July 3) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DUMB AND DUMBER (2): &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   ``He thinks that stuff's for sissies.'' (An unnamed fund-raiser
on George W. Bush's attitude to speech-coaching and teleprompters.
Washington Post, June 25) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; REFORMER WITH RESULTS?: &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Some 56 percent of Texans support Bush for president; but 63
percent of them ``are unable to name any reforms that Bush has
brought about in his state.'' (Scripps Howard Texas poll, June 25) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MINORITY OUTREACH WEEK (1): &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   (1)``Yo quiero mucho.'' (Al Gore telling a group of Latino
leaders that he loves them. New York Times, June 25) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MINORITY OUTREACH WEEK (2): &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   The Republican Party ``is certainly not seen as the black guy's
party.'' (Colin Powell, who would consider serving Bush as his
secretary of state. Fox News, Sunday, June 25) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
