<TEXT>
<P>
   SUMMER IS HERE...
</P>
<P>
   BUT THE LIVING'S NOT ALWAYS EASY
</P>
<P>
   Hiking, boating, swimming, playing softball ... All these
activities are fun, but they can also be dangerous.
</P>
<P>
   You could be happily swimming at the shore, for example, when
suddenly you spot the fin of a shark. Would you know what to do?
</P>
<P>
   You would if you had read ``The WORST-CASE SCENARIO Survival
Handbook,'' a best seller designed to get you through those times
when life suddenly takes a turn for the worse.
</P>
<P>
   If you haven't read it, don't worry. An eight-part series from
the book is available now _ just in time for the summer disaster
season. Each 500-word excerpt includes art:
</P>
<P>
   SNAKE NOT CHARMED? HOW TO SURVIVE AN ATTACK &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CAUGHT IN A `TITANIC' SITUATION? HOW TO SURVIVE ADRIFT AT SEA &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LOOK BEFORE YOU LEAP: HOW TO SURVIVE A JUMP INTO WATER FROM A
BRIDGE OR CLIFF &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HOWDY, SMOKEY. WHAT TO DO IF YOU COME FACE-TO-FACE WITH A BEAR &QL;
</P>
<P>
   `HE'S GOT A GUN!' HOW TO SURVIVE
</P>
<P>
   CAN IT STRIKE TWICE? WHY YOU SHOULD WATCH OUT FOR LIGHTNING &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THEY SHOOT HORSES, DON'T THEY? WHAT TO DO IF YOU BREAK YOUR LEG &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DIDN'T ENJOY `JAWS'? HOW TO FEND OFF A SHARK &QL;
</P>
