   MEXICO-U.S.-BORDER (Edinburg, Texas) _ Five years after the
Clinton administration and the Republican Congress began a massive
law enforcement buildup along the Mexican-U.S. border to fight the
war on drugs and illegal immigration, federal and state courts are
now buckling under the strain of the enormous criminal caseload. By
Jim Yardley.
