the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, a 12-volume, Arabic-language
compendium of a vanishing way of life, has just been printed. Its
authors say the series, which includes 5,000 drawings,
illustrations and graphs, is the largest body of secular
scholarship ever produced in Saudi Arabia. By Judith Miller.
