<P>
   DOCTORS-UNIONS (Washington) _ Senate Majority Leader Trent Lott
says he will block Senate action on a House-passed bill sponsored
by Rep. Tom Campbell that would allow doctors to bargain
collectively with health insurers. The measure, which passed the
House early Friday, would give physicians a limited anti-trust
exemption so they could band together to negotiate with health
plans over items such as fees.
</P>
<P>
   By JUDY HOLLAND.
