   Moving on NYT wire in (w) Washington and (f) financial
categories.
</P>
<P>
   SBC-TEXAS _ SBC Communications is on the brink of receiving
federal approval to offer long-distance calling in Texas, which
would mark only the second time a regional Bell telephone company
has secured permission to provide that service to its local
customers. (Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   SPEEDWAY _ TALLAHASSEE _ Jeb Bush decides a day before the Pepsi
400 to award $2 million to Daytona International Speedway, a
private corporation, to build a pedestrian overpass. Last year Bush
vetoed a $3 million line item for the same project and in March, he
indicated his disapproval for a $1.5-million line item in this
year's budget, despite a visit from NASCAR scion Bill France Jr. So
why did Jeb change his mind? He says it's good for economic
development. Coincidentally, his brother and presidential candidate
George W. is the race grand marshal this year. (Date, Palm Beach
Post)
</P>
