<P>
   FBN-MUNOZ _ When he played professional football, Anthony Munoz
had the reputation of standing tall in the pocket. Since leaving
the sport, the Bengals' Hall-of-Famer often seizes the opportunity
to stand tall in the pulpit. Sunday morning, that's where you'll
find him. ( Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   RACING
</P>
<P>
   CAR-DAYTONA-FEATURE _ Whom do you trust? That's the question
WInston Cup Drivers have to ask themselves in Saturday night's 8
p.m. Pepsi 400. The use of restrictor plates forces drivers to
draft more and they have to be able to trust the partner they
choose for this. Dale Jarrett goes for third consecutive victory at
the Daytona track. (Carvell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
