   CANADA-FARMERS (Irishtown, Prince Edward Island) _ European
farmers are finding they can buy land in Canada and the United
States cheaply and make a killing, at the same time that longtime
North American farmers complain they can't make it. By Colin
Nickerson. 1600 words. (i and f coding)
