   TEN-WIMBLEDON (London) _ Andre Agassi puts Todd Martin out of
his misery, 6-4, 2-6, 7-6, 2-6, 10-8, with a display that
illustrates why he is the world's top-ranked male player and
showman. By Bob Duffy. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   TEN-COLLINS-COLUMN (London) _ Deja Vu, who I'd thought was a
famous Romanian tennis player, appears. In Centre Court somebody
said, ``If that's not deja vu, then Todd Martin isn't the tallest
guy to come up short in this precinct.'' By Bud Collins. 1000
words.
</P>
