<P>
   COURT-ROUNDUP (Washington) _ In a term filled with emotionally
charged cases, some Supreme Court justices took surprisingly
different positions from those they had taken in the past. Their
ideological fence-jumping mirrored the conflicts that the public
still has with such issues as abortion, police power and separation
of church and state. By MARK HELM. (Filed Friday.)
</P>
<P>
   MISSILE-DEFENSE (Washington) _ A 37-year-old Minuteman missile
will roar out of a central California silo next Friday heading west
over the Pacific in a $100 million test of a new weapon that will
try to knock the missile down. The test of a scaled-back successor
to a weapon in President Ronald Reagan's Star Wars plan, could have
crucial ramifications for U.S. defense strategy. We describe the
test, how it will work and what it will mean for U.S.-Russia and
U.S.-China relations. By ERIC ROSENBERG. (Filed Friday
</P>
