<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mix-and-match line great for office, travel
 &HT;    By Meredith Moss
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ Casual Corner's Collection of mix-and-match,
wrinkle-resistant separates appears to be a hit.
</P>
<P>
   According to Linda Waldrop, assistant manager of Casual Corner
at the Dayton Mall, the line _ introduced in December 1998 _ is
popular with career women and those who travel or need
special-occasion outfits.
</P>
<P>
   The pieces, made of acetate/polyester, come in black and navy
and are carried year-round for seasonless dressing. New colors and
pieces are added each season.
</P>
<P>
   This summer's camouflage collection includes animal-print matte
jersey separates that go with dark olive and black. You can pair a
3/4-length-sleeve animal-print shirt and tank with an olive pencil
skirt or pair a solid-black 3/4-length-sleeve shirt with a black
sleeveless sheath for a look that will take you to dinner.
</P>
<P>
   There's also a new four-piece group of soft pinstripes that
includes a 3/4-length-sleeve shirt-collar jacket, tunic tank, short
slim skirt and pants. Add a splash of color with a lime-and-black
polka dot silk blouse.
</P>
<P>
   Pieces range from $49 for a short skirt to $119 for a long
jacket.
</P>
<P>
   There's also a Casual Corner store at the Mall at Fairfield
Commons.
</P>
<P>
   LANE BRYANT ENCOURAGING VOTE
</P>
<P>
   Plus-size retailer Lane Bryant is launching a promotion Tuesday
designed to encourage young women to register to vote.
</P>
<P>
   According to the Federal Election Commission, nearly 60 million
eligible voters remain unregistered. Women are invited to ``click
and be heard'' by logging on to www.lanebryant.com and registering
to vote.
</P>
<P>
   The campaign is co-sponsored by election.com, an online election
company.
</P>
<P>
   Newly appointed spokesperson for Lane Bryant is hip-hop's Queen
Latifah, who will make her runway debut at Lane Bryant's Fall 2000
Venezia Jeans Fashion Show in September in New York. She was chosen
as a role model for plus-size women based on her ``strength,
personal style and activism for a wide range of causes.''
</P>
<P>
   SPA WORKERS FIND USES FOR VASELINE
</P>
<P>
   A jar of Vaseline has been a skin-care staple for years. So
Vaseline invited America's fancy spas to create ``Spa in a Jar''
formulas using petroleum jelly. The spas created their recipes in
exchange for a donation made to Cancer Care Inc., a national
charity for cancer patients and their caregivers.
</P>
<P>
   _ This one is from Helen Famulare, esthetician at Elizabeth
Arden Red Door Salon and Spa in New York City:
</P>
<P>
   For an after-sun skin soother, mix 2 tablespoons of aloe vera
(plant form) with 1/4 cup of Vaseline before bedtime. Apply with
light massage to sunburned areas until absorbed. Mix a fresh batch
for each use. Designed to keep skin moist and fresh and to calm
sunburn.
</P>
<P>
   _ This recipe is from Carla Stoehr, massage therapist at the
Golden Door in Telluride, Colo.:
</P>
<P>
   For a foot scrub, fill a bathtub with warm water. (You'll soak
your feet in the tub 10-15 minutes before applying the mixture
you're about to make.) Briefly warm 1/4 cup Vaseline in a bowl (a
double boiler is best _ do not microwave). Test to be sure it isn't
too hot. In a larger bowl, mix 1/4 cup Epsom or sea salts with two
to four drops of your favorite essential oil. Add warm Vaseline to
the mixture and mix well.
</P>
<P>
   Soak your feet in the tub to soften them. Then exfoliate feet
with the Vaseline mixture and finish with a steamed cloth scented
with your favorite oil.
</P>
<P>
   _ This recipe is from Meghan Brady, head spa technician at The
Spa at the Sporting Club in San Diego:
</P>
<P>
   For silky smooth legs, mix 1/4 cup Vaseline Petroleum Jelly with
1/2 cup Vaseline Intensive Care Lotion. After shaving in the
shower, apply mixture to legs.
</P>
<P>
   CELEBRITY HANDBAGS TO BE AUCTIONED
</P>
<P>
   Breast Cancer Care is the recipient of an upcoming on-line
handbag auction.
</P>
<P>
   Celebrities have donated their purses to www.handbag.com, a
women's interest Web site, which will hold its first ever online
auction from July 3-13.
</P>
<P>
   According to the Web site, Margaret Thatcher is among the 15
women who have given handbags to the charity auction.
</P>
<P>
   SHISEIDO COSMETICS HELPS SKIN CANCER GROUP
</P>
<P>
   Shiseido Cosmetics is conducting a two-week program to increase
awareness of skin cancer and raise money for its prevention and
cure.dation brochure as well as a newsletter.
</P>
<P>
   You'll find the cosmetics line at Lazarus at the Dayton Mall.
Check out Shiseido's Eyebrow Shapeliner ($20.50). The specially
designed comb imparts translucent color to match your natural brow
color.
</P>
