<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, June 28
about groups that disagreed with the Supreme Court ruling allowing
the Boy Scouts of America to exclude gays misstated the position of
the United Methodist Church. Although the church opposes
discrimination based on sexual orientation, it did not encourage
congregations to sever ties with the Boy Scouts.  &QL;
